&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Cloudflare provides reasonable accommodations to qualified individuals with disabilities. &amp;nbsp;Please tell us if you require a reasonable accommodation to apply for a job. Examples of reasonable accommodations include, but are not limited to, changing the application process, providing documents in an alternate format, using a sign language interpreter, or using specialized equipment. &amp;nbsp;If you require a reasonable accommodation to apply for a job, please contact us via e-mail at &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;hr@cloudflare.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt; or via mail at 101 Townsend St. San Francisco, CA 94107.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Cloudflare, we are on a mission to help build a better Internet. Today the company runs one of the world’s largest networks that powers millions of websites and other Internet properties for customers ranging from individual bloggers to SMBs to Fortune 500 companies. Cloudflare protects and accelerates any Internet application online without adding hardware, installing software, or changing a line of code. Internet properties powered by Cloudflare all have web traffic routed through its intelligent global network, which gets smarter with every request. As a result, they see significant improvement in performance and a decrease in spam and other attacks. Cloudflare was named to Entrepreneur Magazine’s Top Company Cultures list and ranked among the World’s Most Innovative Companies by Fast Company.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Cloudflare, we’re not looking for people who wait for a polished roadmap; we’re looking for the builders who see the cracks in the Internet that everyone else has simply learned to live with. We value candidates who have the instinct to spot a &quot;normalized&quot; problem and the AI-native curiosity to create a solution using the latest tools. Our culture is built on iteration, leveraging AI to ship faster today to make it better tomorrow, while ensuring that every improvement, no matter how small, is shared across the team to lift everyone up. If you’re the type of person who values curiosity over bureaucracy, and that AI is a partner in solving tough problems to keep the Internet moving forward, you’ll fit right in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Location: SF Bay Area&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the &lt;strong&gt;Business Insights and Planning Manager&lt;/strong&gt;, you will partner across the Americas Sales and Revenue Operations teams to accelerate growth through strategic analytics and planning. This is a high-impact revenue intelligence position focused on generating insights and influencing execution. A critical component of this role is serving as the primary advocate for the Americas, representing regional performance and requirements to global teams to drive cross-functional alignment. You will translate complex data into clear, actionable decisions across the revenue organization, acting as a self-starter who can manage independent workstreams while serving as a trusted thought partner to leadership.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Revenue Insights: Conduct hypothesis-driven analysis to identify trends and risks. Move beyond &quot;what happened&quot; to clearly articulate &quot;why,&quot; recommending specific commercial actions to accelerate growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual Sales Planning &amp;amp; Modeling: Lead the analytical engine for annual planning, including quota and capacity modeling, and provide data-driven recommendations for territory segmentation to optimize sales coverage.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executive Presentation: Build compelling data packs and decks for quarterly business reviews (QBRs), strategic planning and pipeline generation reviews, presenting key regional performance insights to senior and VP-level stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Revenue Intelligence Framework: Support and refine the end-to-end revenue intelligence model, ensuring a unified view across pipeline, bookings, funnel performance, and sales onboarding.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Metric Clarity &amp;amp; Data Stewardship: Drive metric consistency across Salesforce, Google Suite, Forecasting tools. Lead data cleanup initiatives to ensure high-quality inputs and partner with global teams to improve data usability.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Global Alignment &amp;amp; Representation: Serve as the lead voice for the Americas in global forums; ensure regional nuances are represented in global reporting frameworks and drive alignment between regional execution and global strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Audience-Scaled Communication: Deliver tailored insights ranging from simple, actionable signals for field sales to high-level trend implications and strategic choices for the executives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Desirable Skills, Knowledge, and Experience&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional Experience: 8+ years of experience in Sales/Revenue Operations, Revenue Intelligence, or Management Consulting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education: Bachelor’s Degree in Business, Finance, Economics, Analytics, Data Science, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Proficiency: Advanced proficiency in Google Suite, Power BI and Excel (including SQL, data modeling, and DAX) to perform complex performance analysis across multiple systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI Leverage: Demonstrated ability to leverage AI tools to accelerate data analysis, automate reporting workflows, and enhance the speed of insight generation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Planning Expertise: Direct experience in sales capacity modeling, quota setting, and account segmentation methodologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executive Presence: Proven ability to influence senior stakeholders and represent regional interests effectively within a complex, matrixed global organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice-to-Have Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working within a high-growth SaaS company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with the &quot;Modern Revenue Stack&quot; (e.g., Salesforce, Gainsight, Boostup, or Clari).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading cross-regional projects or global data standardization initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compensation may be adjusted depending on work location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For Bay Area based hires: Estimated annual salary of $138,000 - $190,000.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Equity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is eligible to participate in Cloudflare’s equity plan.&lt;/p&gt;
