&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Cloudflare, we are on a mission to help build a better Internet. Today the company runs one of the world’s largest networks that powers millions of websites and other Internet properties for customers ranging from individual bloggers to SMBs to Fortune 500 companies. Cloudflare protects and accelerates any Internet application online without adding hardware, installing software, or changing a line of code. Internet properties powered by Cloudflare all have web traffic routed through its intelligent global network, which gets smarter with every request. As a result, they see significant improvement in performance and a decrease in spam and other attacks. Cloudflare was named to Entrepreneur Magazine’s Top Company Cultures list and ranked among the World’s Most Innovative Companies by Fast Company.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Cloudflare, we’re not looking for people who wait for a polished roadmap; we’re looking for the builders who see the cracks in the Internet that everyone else has simply learned to live with. We value candidates who have the instinct to spot a &quot;normalized&quot; problem and the AI-native curiosity to create a solution using the latest tools. Our culture is built on iteration, leveraging AI to ship faster today to make it better tomorrow, while ensuring that every improvement, no matter how small, is shared across the team to lift everyone up. If you’re the type of person who values curiosity over bureaucracy, and that AI is a partner in solving tough problems to keep the Internet moving forward, you’ll fit right in.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Locations: &lt;/strong&gt;Austin, TX, New York, San Francisco&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Cloudflare&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Cloudflare, our mission is bold yet simple: to help build a better Internet. Our global network handles trillions of requests each month, protecting and accelerating applications without added hardware, software, or code changes. Our Developer Platform, including Workers, Workers AI, R2, KV, Durable Objects, and Pages, empowers developers to build and deploy applications globally, faster than ever before.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Developer GTM organization is a startup within Cloudflare, driving how we attract, inspire, and grow the next generation of builders. We are redefining what developer acquisition looks like in a world where AI and distributed agents are reshaping the stack. Our mission is to create new pathways for developers to discover Cloudflare, whether through ecosystem partnerships, high impact content, or creative field engagement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are builders, storytellers, and connectors united by one goal: to make Cloudflare the most exciting place for developers to build.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Cloudflare is seeking an experienced and strategic Director of Growth Programs to build and scale a comprehensive ecosystem that drives top-of-funnel growth and adoption for our Developer Platform with the goal of ensuring Cloudflare is the default starting point for every student, founder, and innovator. We don’t just provide infrastructure; we provide the launchpad for the next generation of great AI companies.This individual will be responsible for identifying, building, and managing strategic partnerships across educational institutions, startup accelerators, venture capital firms, and other high-leverage growth partners. The ideal candidate has a proven track record in developing global partnership strategies, excellent relationship management skills, and a deep understanding of the developer ecosystem.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you will do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partnership Strategy &amp;amp; Execution:&lt;/strong&gt; Define, develop, and execute a global partnership strategy focused on increasing developer platform usage, user acquisition, and overall brand presence within target communities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ecosystem Development:&lt;/strong&gt; Build and maintain deep relationships with key external stakeholders, including:&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Startup/Venture Capital/Accelerators:&lt;/strong&gt; Establish partnerships that provide high-potential startups with platform credits, mentorship, and resources, while driving adoption and awareness within top-tier VC and accelerator networks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Educational Institutions:&lt;/strong&gt; Secure partnerships with universities to integrate the Cloudflare Developer Platform into curriculums and student programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Growth Partners:&lt;/strong&gt; Identify global partnerships that expand reach and drive demand generation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; Work closely with Marketing, Sales, and Developer Relations teams on partnership execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Negotiation and Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead all aspects of the partnership lifecycle, from initial prospecting and negotiation of agreements to ongoing relationship management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Program Management: &lt;/strong&gt;Lead and execute programs from inception to scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Who you are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12+ years of experience in business development, strategic partnerships, or corporate development, preferably within a high-growth SaaS or developer-focused technology company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated success in building and scaling partnerships from the ground up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep familiarity with the global startup, venture capital, and developer education ecosystems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional negotiation, communication, and presentation skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to think strategically, execute tactically, and work effectively in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
