&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Director, Partner Solutions Engineering EMEA&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Partner Solutions Engineering organization is dedicated to developing Cloudflare’s partner ecosystem into trusted technical leaders and champions. Our strategy is built on three core pillars: &lt;strong&gt;Align, Build, Accelerate&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Align:&lt;/strong&gt; Work closely with partners to align on Cloudflare’s mission, vision, and overall strategy, ensuring shared priorities and long-term direction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build:&lt;/strong&gt; Develop technical excellence through scalable practices, enablement programs, and reference architectures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accelerate:&lt;/strong&gt; Drive joint growth through active deal and field engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We go beyond enablement—cultivating true technical champions who influence outcomes, accelerate adoption, and deliver differentiated value to customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the &lt;strong&gt;Director of Partner Solutions Engineering for EMEA&lt;/strong&gt;, you will own the regional partner technical strategy and lead the shift from reactive support to proactive, strategic partner acceleration. You will lead and develop a high-performing team of Partner SEs who architect solutions, strengthen partner capabilities, and drive measurable business impact.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Act as the EMEA Partner Technical Business Owner:&lt;/strong&gt; Own the end-to-end partner technical strategy for the region, ensuring tight alignment between Cloudflare’s vision, partner priorities, and joint GTM motions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Partner Development and Acceleration (Align, Build, Accelerate):&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Align:&lt;/strong&gt; Define and execute technical business plans for the region’s top strategic partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Build:&lt;/strong&gt; Establish scalable enablement, reference architectures, and technical best practices that elevate partner delivery and solution quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Accelerate:&lt;/strong&gt; Drive partner-led revenue by moving partners from basic delivery support to full technical and strategic ownership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Technical Revenue Acceleration:&lt;/strong&gt; Engage directly in high-impact deals alongside Sales and partners to accelerate services revenue and strategic wins.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own Pipeline Development and Progression: &lt;/strong&gt;Drive partner-influenced pipeline creation, progression, and closure by embedding Partner SEs into deal strategy, technical validation, and late-stage execution across EMEA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Foster Product Innovation:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as a key feedback conduit between EMEA partners, field teams, and Business Units (BUs), influencing product enhancements that address partner and customer needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Excellence:&lt;/strong&gt; Drive operational rigor and best practices across the Partner SE organization by standardizing processes, clarifying ownership, and enabling the team to focus on high-impact Align, Build, and Accelerate initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Coach and Elevate:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead, mentor, and grow a world-class Partner SE team, emphasizing technical excellence, strategic thinking, and executive-level partner engagement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate Cross-Functionally:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner closely with regional Sales, Product, and GTM leadership to design and execute initiatives that drive scalable, repeatable growth across EMEA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You are a strategic, hands-on leader who blends deep technical insight with strong business judgment. You thrive in building teams, scaling programs, and transforming how partners engage technically.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You bring:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leadership Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; 15+ years of proven experience leading pre-sales, solutions engineering, or partner engineering teams in high-growth enterprise environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Vision:&lt;/strong&gt; A demonstrated ability to shift teams from reactive support to proactive, strategic partnership and end-to-end services ownership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt; Strong background or curiosity in Zero Trust / SASE, Network Security (DDoS, WAF), and cloud or edge computing technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Executive Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; Ability to engage senior executives and C-level stakeholders with clarity, confidence, and influence, translating complex technical concepts into actionable business decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Rigor:&lt;/strong&gt; Experience managing performance metrics, technical wins, and services planning to drive measurable outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
