&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Department&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Cloudflare Gateway team builds the tools that keep the world’s largest enterprises secure. As part of Cloudflare One, our team is responsible for developing high-performance security services that intercept and inspect traffic at the edge. We operate at a massive scale, processing millions of requests per second to protect users from malware, phishing, and data exfiltration. We are a team of curious, principled engineers who value transparency and technical excellence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an Engineering Manager for the Gateway team, you will lead a group of talented software engineers dedicated to both scaling our security products and driving the development of new features. You will be responsible for the growth and well-being of your team, the delivery of complex technical roadmaps, and the reliability of services that our customers depend on every second. You will act as a bridge between product requirements and technical execution, ensuring we build sustainable, high-quality systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;People Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Mentor and coach a diverse team of engineers, fostering a culture of continuous learning, psychological safety, and high performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Delivery:&lt;/strong&gt; Own the end-to-end execution of the team’s roadmap, ensuring projects are delivered with high quality and align with Cloudflare’s long-term architectural goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; Partner closely with Product Management and diverse stakeholders across the company to define requirements, prioritize the backlog, and communicate progress.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Excellence:&lt;/strong&gt; Drive improvements in system reliability and on-call health, ensuring the team maintains high availability for mission-critical gateway services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills &amp;amp; Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proven Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Experience managing software engineering teams, preferably in a fast-paced environment, with a track record of developing talent and leading through technical challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; Ability to explain complex technical concepts to both technical and non-technical audiences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Mindset:&lt;/strong&gt; Experience maintaining production services and a commitment to building observable, reliable systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Systems Expertise:&lt;/strong&gt; Deep understanding of distributed systems, networking protocols (TCP/IP, HTTP/S, DNS), or high-performance proxy technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Stack:&lt;/strong&gt; Familiarity with Rust or Go.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Domain Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; Background in the cybersecurity or Zero Trust space.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Experience managing remote or geographically distributed teams.&lt;/li&gt;
