&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Cloudflare, we have a big vision: to help build a better Internet. We’re looking for a bright, proactive, and detail-oriented &lt;strong&gt;Executive Assistant&lt;/strong&gt; to support our VP of Capacity Planning and Infrastructure and our VP of Infrastructure - Network Strategy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you aren’t just managing a calendar; you are the &quot;central point person&quot; ensuring our leaders stay organized, prioritized, and productive as we scale. This requires a seasoned professional who understands the importance of the EA role in supporting our leaders and prides themselves on building the internal and external relationships necessary to get things done.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Strategic Gatekeeping:&lt;/strong&gt; Strategically plan long-term calendars with minimal direction, aligning schedules with business priorities. You’ll &quot;play Tetris&quot; with global time zones, prioritizing with purpose and deflecting with tact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operational Excellence:&lt;/strong&gt; Own all travel and logistics—both domestic and international—optimizing for the executive’s time and cost. You’ll handle expense reports through Navan and ensure every detail is secured and up-to-date.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Project Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt; Own small-to-medium projects, creating high-quality presentations and spreadsheets. You’ll track action items for recurring meetings (Weekly, Monthly, All Hands) and ensure owners follow through.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mission Control:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as a trusted communicator who understands the &quot;why&quot; behind business priorities. You’ll prepare agendas and data for meetings, ensuring your executives are equipped with everything they need to succeed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt; Our EA team has a high degree of camaraderie and so the ideal candidate values partnering closely with their peers and fostering teamwork, helping to make Cloudflare a welcoming, inclusive place for everyone.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desired Skills and Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; Typically 6+ years of related experience, ideally in a high-growth environment supporting senior leaders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Problem Solving:&lt;/strong&gt; You are a &quot;skilled specialist&quot; who completes complex tasks in resourceful ways. You anticipate logistical needs before they are explicitly stated.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Communication:&lt;/strong&gt; Excellent verbal and written skills. You can distill complex information into clear language and share relevant info in a way everyone understands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Integrity:&lt;/strong&gt; You act with a high level of discretion, doing the right thing even when it’s hard and focusing on the long-term best interest of the company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Savvy:&lt;/strong&gt; Expert-level knowledge of Google Suite and major airline platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mindset: Personable with a &quot;can-do&quot; attitude. You lead with empathy, assume good intentions, and treat everyone with respect.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
